window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>Blade of the Blue Star - The Duke's Unlikely Heir - Vol 2</p> <p>Reinhardt Blazkowicz has proven himself worthy of attending Aegis Crown Academy. A former demon slayer, adopted heir, and now a rising star among his peers, Reinhardt's journey is far from over. Having survived his first weeks, his next challenge isn't one of strength—it's one of character.</p> <p>Reinhardt finds himself caught between two worlds: the warrior who solves problems with a blade, and the heir whose decisions reflect back on Duke Wilhelm and the people of the Blue Star Duchy. As he balances Legion team practice with student council duties, he discovers that some battles can't be won through force alone.</p> <p>With his loyal roommate Baldric, the merchant princess Xenia, and even the heir to the Empire herself watching his every move, he'll learn that true nobility isn't about bloodlines—it's about keeping your word, even when it can cost you everything.</p> <p>At Aegis Crown Academy, Reinhardt must:</p> <ul> <li>Master the Student Council: Sometimes the hardest choice is between what's right and what's proper.</li> <li>Navigate Noble Politics: When protecting a friend means risking his position, Reinhardt must decide what matters more - protocol or promises.</li> <li>Balance a Personal Life: Face the growing complications between duty to his duchy and his feelings for a merchant's daughter.</li> </ul> <p>But Reinhardt's greatest challenge lies in defining what kind of leader he'll become. After all, what good is being heir to the Blue Star Duchy if you can't protect the people who matter to you?</p>"; 
